I just increased the stars to five. I had the Christmas Maki and it was good as well. Basically, the fish is fresh and drinks are delicious. I also tried the teriyaki again and it was as good as last time. I'd be surprised if people didn't like this place. I've been eating sushi for several years, including in Japan and Korea, and this place was excellent. I had the Tokyo Sunset which was fantastic...fresh and interesting ingredients for a creative combination. The teriyaki was also good with tasty vegetables. The lychee martini was pretty good; I'd never had it before. The miso soup had enough seaweed and tofu but was saltier than traditional miso soup. The decor is whimsical but music can be obnoxious. I'm surprised they have music that literally describes someone f---ing (that word was repeatedly sung) various people when kids were there.
Definitely a spot worth stopping over, the food is fantastic and fresh, the prices are fair and it is consistently neat there. Keep it up.
